Tic-Tac-Toe AI Agent Using Minimax Algorithm

Project Overview

This project implements an AI-powered Tic-Tac-Toe game where a human player competes against an intelligent computer opponent. The AI uses the Minimax algorithm to analyze all possible game states and select the optimal move, making it unbeatable.

Features

- Human vs AI gameplay
- Unbeatable AI using the Minimax algorithm
- Automatic win, loss, and draw detection
- Interactive command-line interface
- Strategic decision-making based on game theory

Technologies Used

- Python 3
- Minimax Algorithm
- Artificial Intelligence Concepts

How It Works

1. The human player makes a move by selecting a position on the board.
2. The AI evaluates all possible future game states using the Minimax algorithm.
3. The AI chooses the best possible move to maximize its chances of winning.
4. The game continues until a player wins or the match ends in a draw.

